opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph
Class LFEdge

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph.LFEdge

public class LFEdge
extends Object

An edge in an LF graph. LF graph edges are directed, containing a source and target vertex as well as an edge label representing the type of relation between the two vertices.

Author:
Scott Martin

equals

public boolean equals(Object o)
Tests whether this edge is equal to another by comparing the source and target vertices by using their LFVertex.equals(Object) methods. If the label is null, it is considered equivalent to the other edge's label only if the other edge's label is also null. Otherwise, the labels are compared using their LFEdgeLabel.equals(Object) method.

Overrides:
equals in class Object
Parameters:
o - The edge to compare this edge to.

toString

public String toString()
Gets a string representation of this edge. For example, if the edge's source is w1@woman, its target is w0@the, and its label is Det, this method returns w1@woman --Det--> w0@the.
